  "body": "### Environment information\r\n\r\n* `brownie` Version: 48d3f182747dc7807c4d6149024b519dd7215061\r\n* `hardhat` Version: 2.1.3-dtt.0 sha512-QWI3LbImf5vyshQzC2nGxzkgtMHsK5BovcWUMgNl3f/0QGCtVRLhTvkA6/FK0f8XhDkFCOHLsJmyRrt4Ao9grg==\r\n* `solc` Version: 0.8.3\r\n* Python Version: 3.9.2\r\n* OS: osx and linux\r\n\r\n### What was wrong?\r\n\r\nI'm testing out swapping ganache-cli for hardhat@dtt on the [argobytes](https://github.com/SatoshiAndKin/argobytes-contracts) repo.\r\n\r\nI then ran `hardhat node --fork https://mynode` and then `brownie test --network mainnet-fork`\r\n\r\nSome of my tests failed with `Transaction gas limit is 12475452 and exceeds block gas limit of 9500000`. This is the mainnet gas limit and not hardhat's limit.\r\n\r\n### Workaround\r\n\r\nAdd this to your hardhat config:\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      blockGasLimit: 14000000\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nBen Hauser, [Mar 30, 2021 at 1:38:50 PM]:\r\nbrownie chooses the gas limit in dev mode by looking at the block gas limit on the last block\r\nso prolly just need to re-evaluate how that works\r\n",
